  <p class="lead">Clones are how you preserve genetics and guarantee consistency. Once you find something worth growing — a phenotype that expresses exactly what you're looking for — cloning is how you keep it. This is my exact process from cut to outdoor transition.</p>

  <h2 id="why-clones">Why Clones Over Seeds</h2>
  <p>Seeds introduce genetic variation — even stable F1s express differently across phenotypes. When you find a plant that hits every mark — structure, vigor, aroma, terpene profile — cloning freezes that expression. Every clone is genetically identical to the mother.</p>
  <p>For outdoor Hawaii grows this matters even more. You're working with a specific climate, specific pest pressure, specific humidity. A proven pheno that thrives in your garden is worth preserving. Seeds are for hunting. Clones are for keeping what you found.</p>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <div class="label">Genetic Consistency</div>
      <p>Every clone is identical to the mother. No phenotype variation, no guessing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <div class="label">Known Traits</div>
      <p>You already know how the plant grows, finishes, and expresses. No surprises.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <div class="label">Time Savings</div>
      <p>Clones skip the seedling stage. Rooted cuts go straight into veg.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <div class="label">Preservation</div>
      <p>Keep elite genetics alive indefinitely through a healthy mother plant program.</p>
    </div>
